Description: Fragment of rectangular handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharp turn. Clay fine pink. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Pencil '813' and worn number, circled Name Archestratos. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0095.36.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1194)
